 dmg rather than just nerfing it to 66%. <br><br>In addition I think individual spells should have 3 new attributes.<br><br>A) pvp dmg modifier so that single spells could be tuned to be stronger or weaker when used on players.  A spell with a 1.5 modifier when used in a situation with 66% spell dmg as per the tables above would do the full listed dmg - resists.<br><br>B) pvp resist modifier to give players more or less chance to resist the spell, I believe there is allready a general attribute that is similar but that it effects both pvp and pve which doesn't allow accurate tuning for pvp.<br><br>C) set resist lvl modifier to be used in place of attribute B for some 50+ spells that would set the base lvl of resist for a spell. In other words the 54 druid nuke scorae might always hit as if the target has x lvl of resist. X being a number that is fair for all parties.<br><br>This set of suggestions is a much better solution than messing around with the modifier for resist debuffs in pvp helping some spells to much some to little.<br><br>The second attribute even adresses an enchanter concern with NOTHING landing. If spells had attribute B certain spells could be given inherently less resistance when used in pvp without making them more powerful in pve or raising the pvp resisted debuff modifier (currently all resistance debuffs do 1.5 normal when used in pvp) to such a ridiculous extent that enc end up blinding, rooting, and owning people.<br><br>In addition the first attribute would provide a clean way to remove mannaburn from the pvp environment as verant has stated is neccesary. Simply set attribute A to 0% of full dmg in pvp.<br><br>Now about HT. Nerf HT to only do a fixed % of a players hp at maximum say 40%.<br><br>Next what about that luclin mask that gives all classes the ability to shadowstep. Remove it.  On blue servers its a trivial ability on reds its a major spell line and should be restricted to the classes that actually get the skill.  <br><br>Fix the charm poofing pets exploit.<br><br>Fix the ds exp kill exploit.  This goes something like this.  In a city where you are an ally you find a target with lower faction.  Cast a small ds on them then melee them once.  Guards in the vicinity will interpret the dmg done to you by the ds you cast as the victim attacking you back and assist most likely exp killing your victim.<br><br>Thoughs? Comments? Suggestions? <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showPrevMessage?topicID=49.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showNextMessage?topicID=49.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=49.topic><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.emailToFriend?topicID=49.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.threadControl?topicID=49.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=49.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=49.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td col